 to the consolidation of some of the most fundamental stereotypes of modern antisemitism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aJewish politicianszGreat BritainvBiography. 0aJewsxSocial conditions. 0aJewszEuropexHistoryy20th century. 0aJewszGreat BritainvBiography. 0aPrime ministerszGreat BritainvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Presidents & Heads of State.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066771440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030022189340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300221893423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300221893/original  a978-3-11-066771-4  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles